{
  "title": "Slayer Shot",
  "author": "Decent",
  "notes": "The signature Slayer Shot is a testament to precision, emphasizing control over Pre-Brew saturation, Total Contact Time (TCT), and balance between body, sweetness and acidity. Following adjustments are required.\n\n1. Adjust Pre-Brew Flow Rate : Default at 1 ml/s. Adjust by ±0.1 ml/s to fully saturate the puck until first drip of coffee within 25-30 seconds.\n\n2. Grind Adjustment : Aim for Total Contact Time (TCT) of 45-55 seconds. Adjust grind size to achieve this:\nA) TCT < 45s: Grind Finer. B) TCT > 55s: Grind Coarser. C) Adjust yield for desired body (lighter or heavier).\n\n3. Balance : A) Too acidic? Grind finer to increase TCT. B) Too bitter? Grind Coarser to decrease TCT.\n\n4. Extended Pre-Brew : Decrease flow rate (eg. -0.1 ml/s) to extend Pre-Brew for enhanced sweetness and reduce acidity. Increase flow rate (eg. +0.1 ml/s) to shorten Pre-Brew and reduce bitterness.\n\nDownloaded from Visualizer",
